!! $testcase widget

The core of explide. `$testcase` creates an isolated sandbox wiki with its own tiddler store. Child `$data` elements define the tiddlers available in the sandbox. The `testcase-output-tiddler` attribute controls which sandbox tiddler is rendered in the Output tab.

!! $genesis widget

Used to dynamically create `$data` elements inside `$testcase`. Explide uses `$genesis` with computed attributes to assemble data tiddlers with remapped `$rri$:` fields at render time, avoiding the need for static markup per tiddler.

!! $data widget

Child of `$testcase` — defines a single tiddler in the sandbox. Attributes become tiddler fields. Explide generates one `$data` per imported shadow tiddler, explide data tiddler, and ad-hoc tiddler.

!! ViewTemplate integration

The file `core-integration/ViewTemplate.tid` is tagged `$:/tags/ViewTemplate`. It uses a conditional check (`rri.type` = `explide/config`) to inject the IDE below the tiddler body. This is the standard TiddlyWiki pattern for extending how tiddlers render.

!! Shadow tiddler enumeration

Explide uses `[all[shadows]prefix<pluginTitle>]` to enumerate a plugin's shadow tiddlers. The `all[shadows]` operator returns tiddlers that come from installed plugins — these are read-only until overridden by a real tiddler with the same title.

!! code-body: yes

Used on `variables.tid` to tell TiddlyWiki to parse the body as function/procedure definitions rather than renderable wikitext.

